---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import PrivacyStrip from '../../components/PrivacyStrip.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { TRAVEL_TOOLS } from '../../data/travel/index';
import { breadcrumbSchema, collectionPageSchema, faqSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Travel & Trips', url: '/travel/' },
];
const faqs = [
  { q: 'Are these travel calculators accurate?', a: 'The geometry is exact: flight distance uses the haversine great-circle formula on a mean Earth radius of 6,371 km, and road-trip and budget maths are straightforward. The estimators (flight time, jet lag, baggage limits, tipping customs) rest on typical real-world figures that vary — each page cites its source and explains the assumptions.' },
  { q: 'Do these use my location or send data anywhere?', a: 'No. Every tool runs entirely in your browser — no location access, no accounts, no currency conversion calls. Your inputs never leave your device, and the tools work offline.' },
  { q: 'Do the tools convert currency?', a: 'No — the tip and budget tools work in whatever currency you type, with no conversion. That keeps them private and offline; live exchange rates would require sending your figures to a server.' },
  { q: 'Can I rely on the baggage and tipping figures?', a: 'Treat them as guidance. Baggage limits vary by airline and fare and tipping is cultural and changes over time, so we show common reference figures with clear caveats — always confirm your specific airline\'s rules, and read the bill for service charges.' },
];
const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  collectionPageSchema({ name: 'Travel & Trips Calculators', url: '/travel/', description: 'Free, private travel calculators: flight distance, flight time, layover, jet lag, tip by country, road-trip time, travel budget and luggage size.', items: TRAVEL_TOOLS.map((t) => ({ name: t.name, url: `/travel/${t.slug}/` })) }),
  faqSchema(faqs),
];
---

<Base
  title="Travel & Trips Calculators — Flight Distance, Jet Lag, Tips | LazyTools"
  description="Free travel calculators that run in your browser: flight distance and time, layover checker, jet lag estimator, tip-by-country, road-trip time, travel budget and luggage size. No location access, no sign-up, no upload."
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-6">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Travel & Trips Calculators</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
      Plan the trip without the spreadsheet — measure the great-circle distance and rough flight time between
      any two cities, check whether a layover is long enough, estimate jet lag, split a restaurant bill with
      customary tips by country, work out road-trip driving time, size a travel budget, and check a bag against
      cabin and checked limits. Everything runs in your browser — no location access, no sign-up.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-5"><PrivacyStrip /></div>

    <section class="mt-8">
      <ul class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {TRAVEL_TOOLS.map((t) => (
          <li>
            <a href={`/travel/${t.slug}/`} class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-4 transition hover:border-brand-400 hover:shadow-sm">
              <span class="text-2xl" aria-hidden="true">{t.icon}</span>
              <span class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">{t.name}</span>
              <span class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">{t.lead.split('—')[0].split('(')[0]}</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="prose-lazy mt-10">
      <h2>From the map to the bill, worked out in your browser</h2>
      <p>
        Trip planning is a pile of small calculations: <em>how far is it, how long will it take, is my
        connection tight, how much will jet lag cost me, what do I tip here, and will my bag fit?</em> These
        tools answer each one directly. The <a href="/travel/flight-distance-calculator/">flight distance
        calculator</a> draws the great-circle route on a world map and reads off the distance, bearing and a
        rough flight time; the <a href="/travel/layover-calculator/">layover checker</a> tells you whether a
        connection clears a typical minimum; and the <a href="/travel/jet-lag-calculator/">jet lag
        calculator</a> turns the time zones you cross into days of adjustment, with tips to shorten them.
      </p>
      <p>
        The everyday-money tools stay honest about what they can and can't do. The
        <a href="/travel/tip-calculator/">tip calculator</a> and <a href="/travel/travel-budget-calculator/">budget
        planner</a> work in whatever currency you type — <strong>no conversion, nothing sent to a server</strong> —
        because private, offline maths matters more than a live exchange rate you can look up separately. The
        distances and flight times are great-circle estimates, and the baggage and tipping figures are common
        references that vary by airline and country, so we cite sources and flag the assumptions on every page.
        For the raw unit maths behind a trip, see the <a href="/units/">Units</a> and <a href="/calculators/">Calculators</a>
        categories.
      </p>
    </section>

    <FaqSection faqs={faqs} />
  </div>
</Base>
